planets.name: Mercury
planets.description: The smallest and closest planet to the Sun in the Solar System.

planets.name: Venus
planets.description: The second planet from the Sun and the hottest planet in the Solar System.

planets.name: Earth
planets.description: The third planet from the Sun and the only planet known to support life.

planets.name: Mars
planets.description: The fourth planet from the Sun, often referred to as the 'Red Planet'.

planets.name: Jupiter
planets.description: The largest planet in the Solar System, known for its Great Red Spot.

planets.name: Saturn
planets.description: The sixth planet from the Sun, famous for its prominent ring system.

planets.name: Uranus
planets.description: The seventh planet from the Sun, known for its bluish-green color.

planets.name: Neptune
planets.description: The eighth and farthest known planet from the Sun, noted for its deep blue color.
